# Soundboard Mappings v3 - Example Configuration
# Format: page_id,button,event,action[,param1]
# Trailing columns are optional (no trailing commas needed)
#
# Page IDs: String identifiers (max 31 chars), e.g., "default", "fx", "music"
#           First page loaded becomes the active page on startup.
#           Encoder switch toggles between VOLUME and PAGE modes.
#           In PAGE mode, encoder rotation cycles through pages.
#
# Action types and parameters:
# - stop: No parameters
# - play: file (play once until EOF)
# - play_cut: file (play once, stop on RELEASE)
# - play_lock: file (press=play with stop on release, long_press=lock)
#
# Button Layout (4x3 matrix, row-major numbering):
#   +---+---+---+
#   |10 |11 |12 |  Row 3
#   +---+---+---+
#   | 7 | 8 | 9 |  Row 2
#   +---+---+---+
#   | 4 | 5 | 6 |  Row 1
#   +---+---+---+
#   | 1 | 2 | 3 |  Row 0
#   +---+---+---+
#
# Event types: press, long_press, release
# Volume: Controlled via rotary encoder (not mappable to buttons)
# Encoder: Short press toggles VOLUME/PAGE mode. Rotation adjusts volume or changes page.

# ============================================================================
# Page "default": Sound Effects & Basic Actions
# ============================================================================

# Button 1: Simple laser sound (plays once, no interrupt)
default,1,press,play,laser.wav

# Button 2: Explosion with auto-stop on release
default,2,press,play_cut,explosion.wav

# Button 3: Gunshot with play_lock behavior
# Quick press+release: plays then stops (like play_cut)
# Hold past long_press threshold then release: keeps playing (locked)
# Press again while locked: stops playback
default,3,press,play_lock,gunshot.wav

# Button 4: Siren with play_lock
default,4,press,play_lock,siren.wav

# Button 5: Alarm sound
default,5,press,play,alarm.wav

# Button 6: Background music with play_lock (hold to lock, press again to stop)
default,6,press,play_lock,background_music.wav

# Button 7: Jingle (play once)
default,7,press,play,jingle.wav

# Button 8: Simple beep
default,8,press,play,beep.wav

# Button 9: Multi-action button (different sounds for press vs long_press)
default,9,press,play,short_alert.wav
default,9,long_press,play,long_alarm.wav

# Button 10: Horn (play while held)
default,10,press,play_cut,horn.wav

# Button 11: Whoosh sound
default,11,press,play,whoosh.wav

# Button 12: Stop playback
default,12,press,stop

# ============================================================================
# Page "music": Music tracks (switch to this page via encoder)
# ============================================================================

music,1,press,play_lock,song1.wav
music,2,press,play_lock,song2.wav
music,3,press,play_lock,song3.wav

# Voice clips on same page
music,4,press,play,voice1.wav
music,5,press,play,voice2.wav
music,6,press,play,voice3.wav

# ============================================================================
# Notes:
# ============================================================================
# - Page IDs are strings (e.g., "default", "music", "fx") - max 31 characters
# - First page in file becomes active on startup
# - Encoder switch short press: toggles between VOLUME and PAGE modes
# - In PAGE mode, encoder rotation cycles through pages (circular)
# - Button release events: Automatically handled for play_cut and play_lock
# - play_lock: long_press while playing locks playback (implicit, no CSV mapping needed)
# - Multiple mappings per button: Use different events (press, long_press, release)
# - Audio files: Place WAV files in /sdcard/ or /spiffs/ directories
# - Relative paths (without leading /) are auto-prefixed with /sdcard/
